{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had half-tracks, which is half armored and half wheels, as well as regular cross-country ambulances, Jeeps, weapons carrier.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to learn weapons convoy discipline, care of the wounded under difficult situations, blackout, how to set up an aid station in the forest or in a cellar or something and black it out from enemy air and enemy patrols, and front line surgery.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we were very front line, so what we did was pretty fast.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "12th Armored Division.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The final man who took us into battle was Roderick Allen, General Roderick Allen.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mostly Northerners.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were from Pennsylvania, Illinois.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had some hillbillies from the Appalachian area and a few Texans, who always took a lot of ribbing, because we sent-- our second year training was at Camp Barkeley, Texas, west of Abilene, which is a pretty dismal place, as we never tired pointing out to the Texans in our division.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Many of them in the medical battalion, the medical-- because many of them had been looking at professional careers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had many Jews in the battalion as medical officers and dental officers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then scattered through the division was about-- a pretty good cross-section of American population, except for the fact that we were segregated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were no blacks at that point.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a segregated Army in World War II.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, let me think.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were three infantry battalions, which had two surgeons each.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's six.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were three tanks with one man each, which is nine.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Excuse me, I've been fighting the flu.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Three artillery battalions would be 12.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there were about-- one in the recons, 13.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the medical battalion, there were 3 companies, 12-- 20-some physicians total, I would guess in the division.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
